post_text: Hettinger Public School will be participating in the emergency food program beginning Tuesday, September 8th (free meals will be retroactive to August 31) . This will allow all enrolled students to receive free breakfast and lunch during the day. This is a grant through the USDA and will run until December 31 or until funding is no longer available. We still NEED you to complete free and reduced forms, this is the mechanism that is used for our federal grants, such as the free fruit and vegetable program and the after school program among others. We will send out more information as we finalize the details and procedures. If you have questions please call Ryan Moser at 567-5315. Thank you for your support during these ever changing times.

post_text: The Board Meeting scheduled on Monday, July 27 at 6pm is an open public meeting. However, an executive session is on the agenda, this session is used to strategize for negotiations. The executive session may or may not be necessary, but needs to be on the agenda so the public is informed about the possibility of using the session. NO motions can be made during an executive session, this would be done in public after the executive session. HPS will set up a zoom as soon as possible to accommodate those who wish to attend via distance, please check our website and FB page for the updated postings.

post_text: The Hettinger Public School Board invites the public to participate in a school demographic planning meeting to fulfill requirements under NDCC 15.1-07-26. This open public meeting will be held on Wednesday, August 12 at Hettinger Public School, Room 120 beginning at 5:00 pm. At this forum, the school board will discuss and receive public input on how three- and five-year demographics may impact academic and extracurricular programs, instructional and administrative staffing, facility needs and utilization, district tax levies, and the district’s strategic plan.
text: The Hettinger Public School Board invites the public to participate in a school demographic planning meeting to fulfill requirements under NDCC 15.1-07-26. This open public meeting will be held on Wednesday, August 12 at Hettinger Public School, Room 120 beginning at 5:00 pm. At this forum, the school board will discuss and receive public input on how three- and five-year demographics may impact academic and extracurricular programs, instructional and administrative staffing, facility needs and utilization, district tax levies, and the district’s strategic plan.

post_text:
Hettinger Public School has completed a needs assessment of the existing school. The School Board has selected projects that they feel are necessary to building operations; which many discussions about focusing on the immediate and vital needs have occurred.

However, there are community members who have been asking about a new school, and HPS felt they should have a voice in a survey. The direction the Board would like to see is taking care of what the community feels are the highest priorities, the reason for our survey to the community.

The idea of a new school came from community members, not Board leadership, but again, the Board felt it is important to include community voice in the survey. If you have any questions, please contact the school.
